**Summary:** The sample provides example code for all features of the Autodesk Fabrication API from working with Job Items to interacting with the database.

Each of the provided Autodesk Fabrication samples contains both the source code and the compiled assemblies along with any dependencies required. Each sample contains a folder named "Compiled" containing all the files required to run the addin, without the need to build the code yourself.

To run the sample in CADmep using the AutoCAD Plug-in framework copy the folder ACAD\\FabricationSample.bundle to C:\\ProgramData\\Autodesk\\ApplicationPlugins and add the files from the folder named “Compiled” from the build directory. A button named “Fabrication Sample” will be visible on the “Add-Ins” tab which will run the sample when clicked, this requires CADmep to be loaded.

To run the sample in ESTmep or CAMduct, copy the files from the “C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Fabrication 2021\\SDK\\Samples\\CSharp\\FabricationSample\\Compiled” folder into C:\\ProgramData\\Autodesk\\Fabrication\\Addins\\2021.
